channel.title: Double Date Podcast
channel.description: Shane Mauss, a self-described “gangle-puss” (adj. a gangly snuggle-puss) with a penchant for animal mating behavior and science facts and April Macie, a self-denied “angry feminist” (Betty Freidan in a bikini) met on a bus… SHANE: “You can’t just say we met on a bus!” APRIL: “It was a bus!!” SHANE: “People are going to think we met on a Greyhound.” APRIL: “Okay! We met on a DAMN tour bus!” Anyway, after dating for a little over a year, these two professional touring comedians and lovers are running out of things to say to one another and are in the market for new couple friends to squelch their boredom. DOUBLE DATE is a weekly 30-50 minute podcast/ application for couple friends that will cover topics like: Sex, relationships, religion, politics, evolutionary psychology (mostly Shane), and women’s rights (mostly April). Listen weekly as these two talk with another couple in an attempt to push social boundaries and slowly dismantle their own relationship in a desperate bid for attention.
